30 NOVEMBER 2015
GALE WARNING: IN OPERATION ISSUED 1700/30-11-2015.
SMALL CRAFT WARNING: IN OPERATION ISSUED 1700/30-11-2015.
METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 1500: A COLD FRONT NOW SLOW-MOVING ALONG THE
SOUTH COAST WILL TRANSFORM TO A WARM FRONT EARLY TONIGHT AND EXTEND NORTHEASTWARDS
ACROSS ALL AREAS BEFORE TUESDAY MORNING THE LIGHT NORTHERLY AIRFLOW OVER
MOST AREAS WILL BECOME STRONG SOUTHWESTERLY GENERALLY AS THE NIGHT GOES
ON.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM CARNSORE POINT TO DUNGARVAN TO MIZEN HEAD -WIND:
SOUTHWEST FORCE 5 TO 7 INCREASING GALE FORCE 8 AT TIMES WEST OF ROCHE'S
POINT OVERNIGHT.WEATHER: OUTBREAKS OF RAIN OR DRIZZLE WITH FOG PATCHES DEVELOPING.VISIBILITY:
MODERATE OCCASIONALLY POOR.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM MIZEN HEAD TO MALIN HEAD TO CARNSORE POINT AND
THE IRISH SEA -WIND: NORTHWEST TO NORTH FORCE 3 OR 4 BECOMING SOUTHWEST
OVERNIGHT AND STEADILY INCREASING FORCE 6 TO GALE FORCE 8 BY MORNING STRONGEST
BETWEEN MIZEN HEAD AND FAIR HEAD.WEATHER: SHOWERS IN THE NORTH FOR A TIME
OTHERWISE RAIN AND DRIZZLE ON MUNSTER COASTS BECOMING WIDESPREAD OVERNIGHT
WITH FOG DEVELOPING IN THE WEST ALSO BECOMING MAINLY FAIR ON EASTERN COASTS
DURING TUESDAY.VISIBILITY: MODERATE TO POOR IN RAIN DRIZZLE AND FOG BUT
GOOD IN THE NORTH AND EAST EARLY AND LATE.
WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL: FOR A TIME TONIGHT ON WESTERN COASTS.
OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 1800 WEDNESDAY 02 DECEMBER 2015: NEAR
GALE TO GALE FORCE SOUTHWEST TO SOUTH WINDS INCREASING TO STRONG GALE FORCE
FOR A TIME IN THE WEST AND NORTHWEST VEERING SOUTHWEST TO WEST ON WEDNESDAY
MORNING AND SOON SLACKENING RAIN DRIZZLE AND FOG IN THE WEST AND NORTHWEST
EXTENDING EAST THEN CLEARING ON WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON.WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL
FOR A TIME TONIGHT ON WESTERN COASTS.
